            Camelot estimates that adopting the proposal could result in a loss of more than &#x00A3;1.28 billion to good causes. I am not taking its brief and suggesting that that figure is necessarily absolutely correct. I have no doubt that we shall take such matters with a pinch of salt. However, a substantial loss on that front seems possible.</p><p>
            The second report was on side betting. I do not know about the impact of that aspect. Clearly, it will divert some of the money that players currently pump into the lottery. The disadvantage is that none of that money will go to good causes, and not much will go to the Treasury, either.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
